text: Reinstated the film incentive program to attract movie projects to our state. Generates millions and creates jobs! #WALeg
Graduation today for 45 new @wastatepatrol troopers. Congratulations and thank you for your service!
#IfIWonTheLottoIWould plug the state budget hole and send lawmakers home!
About to sign the final #WALeg bills. Marathon session. http://t.co/ufnxANdJ
Cases of whooping cough on the rise. Get vaccinated (or revaccinated) especially if you’re around young children.
WA state ranks high in three recent good government awards for transparency and accessibility. http://t.co/kiX9J6zT
Broke stalemate. Compromise reached. Budget done. #WAleg on their way home!
@USNavy to name a new sub the USS Washington. A fitting tribute to our state and our Navy presence.
@space_needle going Galaxy Gold! Feel like a kid again!
Job picture continues to brighten in Washington state—18 months of job growth in the past 19 months. Must continue to strengthen.
Here’s to the @wsdot crews who maintain our roads. Slow down and give them a brake. #GoOrange during #WorkZoneSafety Awareness Week!
Thank you Sen. Lisa Brown for your leadership. You've been a champion for the state and for the ppl of Spokane. #waleg
Whooping cough at epidemic levels in WA state. Announced today new money and more vaccinations to help prevent future illness.
Welcome aboard Twitter @davidagnew44. Look forward to the keen insights that only a Twitter acct can provide!
Thank you President Obama for your strong step on #MarriageEquality. A historic day.
Statement on the President's heartfelt and geniune announcement today: http://t.co/chJwLeSS
Thank you @jeanenersen for last night’s special on Whooping Cough. Educating is essential—if you haven’t been vaccinated please do.
Bridgeport HS wins again! First they were recognized by the White House. Now named Gold Medal HS by US News&World Report--nation’s top 2%!
Five years running! WA named the most bike-friendly state in the nation! Here’s hoping for nicer weather so we can enjoy this success!
WA is now ready to plug in and charge ahead! Opened 10 electric vehicle charging stations today along I-5 and US 2!
June is Great Outdoors Month! Take advantage of our beautiful state parks & recreational opportunities by getting outdoors & being active!
Dug out the first scoop of dirt for the #99tunnel today. Making progress on a new and revitalized downtown waterfront!
91,000 jobs are generated from our Life Sciences cluster! Thank you Novo Nordisk for expanding your important research in our great state!
Announced multi-agency team to respond to tsunami debris on WA beaches. Volunteers, federal support, and collaboration all needed.
Forbes ranks WA in top 10 states to boom in next 5 yrs. Credit aerospace, tech, and export--our focus pays off. http://t.co/hr8Um0T1
At Renton Technical College with an aerospace class learning how to drill and rivet for airplane fabrication! #waaero http://t.co/Yih4x0dl
Next step-drilling and riveting! New engineering slots & STEM training helps fill aero. jobs for our future! #waaero http://t.co/nG3A2UcF
On the 737 production line in Renton where 35 planes a month are being produced! More planes mean more jobs. #waaero
Signing Boeing’s ecoDemonstrator—a 737 devoted to testing cutting edge technologies and biofuels! #waaero http://t.co/CNesStiN
SCOTUS ruling emphasizes need for federal immigration reform. Vitally important to WA's international trade and agriculture economies.
Fantastic Seattle Pride parade yesterday. Thanks to my family and to the thousands of families there standing up for equality! A great day!
SCOTUS gives important relief for thousands of Washingtonians. Glad our amicus brief could help present a case of why coverage is needed.
Just over two years ago today we filed our first brief in the ACA case. Announced it at Cupcake Royale--congrats today Jody Hall!
W/ Gov Kitzhaber today flew over the Columbia River to look at abandoned vessels and urge changes to hold their owners responsible.
Way to go--Seattle became home to history with the arrival of the NASA Shuttle Trainer at Museum of Flight. Will inspire generations!
WA is the most trade dependent state in the nation. Kicked off trade mission today in Ireland on clean energy, hi-tech, aerospace.
Great success today connecting WA companies to Bombardier--the door is open for growth!
Opened booth at Air Show today. Boeing announced amazing orders and we announced more than 160 aero jobs for WA companies.#WAAero
Big day at Farnborough Air Show! WA suppliers Heath Tecna and Pacifica Engineering announce big contracts - and Boeing lands $9.2B deal!
Another huge win for Boeing! 150 737s ordered by United - making the 737 the only commercial jetliner ever to top 10,000 orders. Congrats!
We must continue to protect the Puget Sound. Touring three sites today with success stories—and highlighting need for ongoing vigilance.
Harvesting oysters and clams in Samish Bay! - learning about work being done to restore this critical shellfish area. http://t.co/T06UZ0bG
Puget Sound has 68 state & 8 natl parks, refuges, forests. It accounts for $9.5 billion in travel spending and 88,000 tourism-related jobs.
More than 600 organizations are cleaning up the Puget Sound. The Puget Sound Partnership works with all to set priorities, keep focus.
Sending our thoughts to the people of Aurora this morning. We stand with you in the wake of this tragedy.
Thanks J.P. Patches for the memories. You continue to keep people smiling!
My heart goes out to the family of the lost DNR diver and to the entire DNR team.
Go Team USA! So proud of the Olympians that represent Washington state - I'll be watching!
Shout out to Oak Harbor and Bremerton--home to Washington's two newest Olympic medal winners!
Way to go Nathan Adrian! Washington is proud!
Congratulations to Washington goalkeeper Hope Solo and the US women’s soccer team for winning gold!
Kathi Goertzen was among the finest and most courageous people. She is in my heart and will not be forgotten by her countless friends.
State of Emergency in #taylorbridgefire brings more resources to area in need. Helicopters from nat'l guard to provide fire supression.

Cheering for our talented Washington state Paralympians! Let the Games begin! #paralympics
Happy 50th Birthday Seattle Center – here’s to the #Next50 years of inspiring us toward innovation and the future!

May we #neverforget. Remembering the victims of 9/11 today.
Great news! WA selected again to host internat'l aerospace supplier summit. Similar event last March has already led to $1.3M in new sales!
In response to one of the worst fire situations I’ve seen, I‘ve proclaimed a State of Emergency for counties E. of the Cascades #WaWildfires
Due to fire danger, I've issued a burn ban for E WA. Have to do everything possible to lessen the risk of more fires. http://t.co/nan3q40l

Always amazed at WA potato promotional events! It's no wonder Korea’s our state’s 4th largest trading partner! http://t.co/VwHWen6c
Did you know - WA was recently ranked 1st in the U.S. for seatbelt compliance! Thanks for buckling up and keeping safe on the road.
Still miles to go, but proud to be in a state where we are making progress for our LGBT Washingtonians. #NationalComingOutDay

Celebrated the reopening of Harbor Paper in Grays Harbor today—and the 175 jobs it will bring. A great success story.
We standby ready to help our friends and family impacted by #Sandy. We're prepared to send additional help and resources as needed.
Txt REDCROSS to 90999 to donate $10 for #Sandy disaster relief – there is much to be done and Washingtonians always lend a hand!
Hats off to 48 members of our WA Conservation Corps AmeriCorps on their way to NY tonight to assist with Sandy relief efforts. #SandyRelief
This is it: Vote!
A good night for fairness and equality. MD, ME, MN, and WA. Way to go!
Yesterday Mike and I welcomed our first granddaughter, Audrey, into the world! A great day and a wonderful addition to our family.
Congrats to Gov. Elect Inslee--look forward to a seamless transition. Thank you to AG McKenna for your commitment to public service.
Honoring all of our Veterans--past, present, and future. First Mike and I are humbled by your service and committed to your success.

Remembering those lost to HIV/AIDS. Until there's a cure, we must continue the fight against stigma and discrimination. #WorldAIDSDay.
